{"timestamp": "2025-12-06 09:15:41.877555", "event": "llm_start", "messages": "content='Based on the diagnosis report: Troubleshooting Diagnosis Report\\n\\nExecutive summary\\n- Overall routing and the server farm segment are healthy. OSPF adjacencies and routes appear consistent across core and distribution devices, and the server farm (10.200.0.0/24) is reachable with low latency.\\n- Access domain for core 1/dist 1 is healthy: host_1_1_1_1 has proper IP configuration, default gateway, DNS resolution to local zone, and end-to-end HTTP reachability to the web servers.\\n- Anomaly localized to host_2_1_1_1 in the 10.2.1.0/24 access domain: the host has no IPv4 address or routes configured. Upstream L2/L3 infrastructure for that VLAN/subnet is up and participating in OSPF correctly. Root cause is end-host misconfiguration (missing static IP/default gateway).\\n\\nKey observations and evidence\\n\\n1) End-to-end reachability status\\n- Servers and DNS within 10.200.0.0/24:\\n  - dns_server ↔ web_server_{1,2} pings: 0% loss, ~1–2 ms RTT (from get_reachability).\\n  - web_server_* inter-pings: 0% loss, sub-3 ms RTTs (from get_reachability).\\n  - This confirms the server farm broadcast domain and the server-access router segment are stable.\\n\\n- User host 1 (10.1.1.0/24):\\n  - host_1_1_1_1 → dns_server (10.200.0.2): 0% loss, ~3 ms RTT (functions.ping_pair).\\n  - host_1_1_1_1 → web_server_2 (10.200.0.5): 0% loss, ~2.9 ms avg RTT.\\n  - host_1_1_1_1 → web_server_0 (10.200.0.3): 0% loss, ~2.1 ms avg RTT.\\n  - HTTP tests:\\n    - curl http://10.200.0.3: total ~6–7 ms per request (functions.curl_web_test).\\n    - curl http://web0.local: successful name resolution and HTTP with total ~9 ms (one outlier ~84 ms connect time once).\\n  - host_1_1_1_1 → default gateway (10.1.1.1): 0% loss, ~1.4 ms avg RTT.\\n  - Conclusion: Access 1 path, L3 gateway, DNS resolution for the local zone, and server farm access are healthy.\\n\\n- User host 2 (expected 10.2.1.0/24):\\n  - get_reachability shows host_2_1_1_1 has no IP assigned (null).\\n  - Direct inspection:\\n    - host_2_1_1_1 ip_addr: eth0 UP/LOWER_UP but no IPv4 address; lo only.\\n    - host_2_1_1_1 ip_route: empty.\\n  - Conclusion: End host lacks static IP and default route; cannot participate in IP connectivity.\\n\\n2) L2/L3 device state in the affected path (10.2.1.0/24)\\n- switch_dist_2_1 (distribution/gateway for 10.2.1.0/24):\\n  - br0: 10.2.1.1/24 present (default gateway for the subnet).\\n  - OSPF routes installed:\\n    - O>* 10.1.1.0/24 via 172.16.0.8\\n    - O>* 10.200.0.0/24 via 172.16.0.8\\n    - Core infrastructure subnets via 172.16.0.8\\n  - Interfaces: eth0 172.16.0.9/31 (to core) up; eth1 bridged to br0 up.\\n  - Conclusion: The distribution switch for 10.2.1.0/24 is correctly configured, participating in OSPF, and advertising/receiving routes. Local gateway is up.\\n\\n- Link state at the end host:\\n  - host_2_1_1_1 eth0 is UP/LOWER_UP (so L2 link to access switch is fine), but no IP set.\\n\\n3) OSPF across core and server-access\\n- router_core_{1,2,3} and switch_server_access frr_show_ip_route outputs show:\\n  - All user subnets (10.1.1.0/24 and 10.2.1.0/24) present via expected next hops.\\n  - 10.200.0.0/24 present where appropriate; directly connected on switch_server_access.\\n  - Infrastructure 172.16.0.x/31 routes consistent with topology and expected next-hop adjacency.\\n- No indication of OSPF area or adjacency problems; routes are installed with expected metrics.\\n\\nDetected anomalies\\n- host_2_1_1_1:\\n  - Missing IPv4 address and default route (ip_addr: only lo; ip_route empty).\\n  - In get_reachability, host_2_1_1_1 shows null IP and all tests from this host reported as unknown.\\n\\nLocalization\\n- Fault isolated to the end host host_2_1_1_1 in the 10.2.1.0/24 access domain. The upstream distribution switch (switch_dist_2_1) and core/server-access routing are functioning normally. L2 link to the host is up.\\n\\nRoot cause\\n- End-host misconfiguration: static addressing is required for user hosts, but host_2_1_1_1 has no IPv4 configuration and thus no default gateway or DNS setting. This prevents any IP communication from that host despite the network infrastructure being healthy.\\n\\nImpact assessment\\n- All services reachable from 10.1.1.0/24 and within 10.200.0.0/24 appear normal.\\n- Connectivity issues are confined to host_2_1_1_1 (and potentially any other hosts in 10.2.1.0/24 that are similarly unconfigured)., please provide the submission. Do not submit if no report available.' additional_kwargs={} response_metadata={} id='3fe4e929-88b5-4130-8f52-ecef115793ae'", "model": {"lc": 1, "type": "constructor", "id": ["langchain", "chat_models", "openai", "ChatOpenAI"], "kwargs": {"model_name": "gpt-5", "openai_api_key": {"lc": 1, "type": "secret", "id": ["OPENAI_API_KEY"]}, "stream_usage": true}, "name": "ChatOpenAI"}}
